	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=150995><span id= >Talupus</span></a><br><span id=notbold>48 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Helping out with a shaman epic in COM I was selected due to the warrior there being 4 levels lower than me. However if the warrior were to be the same level or higher or even a level or two under he/she would be the main tank. <br><br>I do agree that Hybrids are better at getting better agro form their spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;But warriors are still at least form my experiences the class selected to MT.<br><br>Warriors are spposed ot be better at it because their AC/HP totals are hgiher than any other class but as an Iksar I have the ac bounus yet, I wear the same armor as all the other SKs so I have about 40 ac more than they do. I have about the same somtiems more ac then warriors of other races at my level. At high end game the extra hp that warriors have helps but when the mobs are hitting for as much as they do the clerics will still be healing the same amount as they would an SK or Paladin surely not any more. I see why warriors are chosen for a few hundred more hp and some ac but IMO I belive that if you want a strong agro to hold SKs and pallys are better for the job. <br><br>Warriors are still picked but perhaps after a series of raids and stuff with SKs and pallys I think that people will see perhaps in the right situation we are better for the job.<br><br>Islude.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
